# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Frontend (Vite) environment — CLIENT-SIDE config only.
#
# Everything here is PUBLIC: it is bundled into the browser app. The Supabase
# anon / "publishable" key is safe to expose — access is enforced server-side by RLS.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your own Supabase project's values.
# (`.env` is gitignored — never commit real values.)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_SUPABASE_URL="https://<your-project-ref>.supabase.co"
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY="<your-supabase-anon-key>"
VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID="<your-project-ref>"

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SERVER-SIDE secrets do NOT belong here.
#
# AI keys (e.g. GEMINI_API_KEY), the service-role key, and anything sensitive live
# as Supabase Edge Function secrets — NOT in this frontend file. Putting them here
# would ship them to every visitor's browser.
#
# Manage them in the Supabase dashboard:
#   Project → Edge Functions → Secrets
# or via the CLI:
#   supabase secrets set GEMINI_API_KEY=... --project-ref <your-project-ref>
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
